Recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to:

start the process and implement appropriate steps that would lead to the closure of the controlled dump and would result to switching to sanitary landfill;

intensify efforts to achieve and embrace the full concept of Ecological Solid Waste Management and adhere to the provisions of R.A. 9003;

discontinue the practice of collecting non-segregated waste and come up with measures that would help its cause.  Encouraging waste segregation at source will also be beneficial in transitioning from an open dumpsite to a sanitary land fill as it would lessen the amount of wastes that would go to this dumpsite; and

adopt scheduling method/scheme which would allow the collection of different types of wastes on different days.

